<text>Potential Energy in Covalent Bond Formation: Reacting Hydrogen and Chlorine Atoms

The bond formed between hydrogen and chlorine is even stronger than that between two hydrogen atoms or two chlorine atoms. Because it is stronger, the amout of chemical potential energy released when this bond is formed will be even more than in the previous reactions. Press the run button to observe this.

 
      

 
